=head1 DESCRIPTION

A complex type that contains information about a Resolver configuration
for a VPC.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AutodefinedReverse => Str

The status of whether or not the Resolver will create autodefined rules
for reverse DNS lookups. This is enabled by default. The status can be
one of following:

=over

=item *

B<ENABLING:> Autodefined rules for reverse DNS lookups are being
enabled but are not complete.

=item *

B<ENABLED:> Autodefined rules for reverse DNS lookups are enabled.

=item *

B<DISABLING:> Autodefined rules for reverse DNS lookups are being
disabled but are not complete.

=item *

B<DISABLED:> Autodefined rules for reverse DNS lookups are disabled.

=back



=head2 Id => Str

ID for the Resolver configuration.


=head2 OwnerId => Str

The owner account ID of the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud VPC.


=head2 ResourceId => Str

The ID of the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud VPC that you're configuring
Resolver for.



